# --- D-PC Messenger .gitignore ---

# 0. Internal AI/team docs (not for public repo)
CLAUDE.md
tasks/
docs/REFACTORING_GUIDELINES_FOR_CLAUDE_CODE.md
archive/

# 1. Environments & Dependencies
# Never commit virtual environments or local dependency caches.
.venv/
venv/
env/
__pypackages__/
node_modules/
poetry.lock

# 2. Secrets & User-Specific Configuration
# NEVER commit sensitive information.
.env
*.env
.env.*
!.env.example
# The user's primary context file. The repository should only contain an example.
personal.json
personal_context.json
dpc_project_plan_phase2.json
dpc_project_plan_phase3.json
FIXES_SUMMARY.md
# The user's private access control rules.
.dpc_access
# The user's cryptographic identity. CRITICAL to ignore.
.dpc/

# 3. Python Generated Files
# Bytecode, caches, and compiled files.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so

# 4. Build, Distribution & Packaging Artifacts
# Files generated when building or distributing the package.
build/
dist/
*.egg-info/
.eggs/
wheels/
*.spec
*.manifest

# 5. Test & Coverage Artifacts
# Reports and caches from testing tools like pytest.
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
.coverage.*
htmlcov/
cover/
.tox/

# 6. IDE & Editor-Specific Files
# Prevents personal editor settings from being committed.
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
.spyderproject
.ropeproject

# 7. OS-Specific Files
# Common files generated by macOS, Windows, and Linux.
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# 8. Log Files
# Never commit logs.
*.log
logs/

# 9. Tool-Specific Caches
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/

# 10. uv / Lock Files
# We DO commit our lock files, so we ensure they are NOT ignored.
# The '!' prefix negates a pattern.
!uv.lock
# !pdm.lock
# !Pipfile.lock

# 11. AI assistant Editor-Specific Files
# Prevents AI personal editor settings from being committed.
.claude/

# 12. Sensitive Legal & Compliance Documents
# Personal legal analysis and compliance docs - keep private
LEGAL_COMPLIANCE_SUMMARY.md
P2P_ARCHITECTURE_LEGAL_DEFENSE.md
GEOGRAPHIC_RESTRICTIONS.md
TERMS_OF_SERVICE.md
COMPUTE_DISCLAIMER.md
docs/LEGAL_COMPLIANCE.md
docs/GEOGRAPHIC_RESTRICTIONS.md
docs/P2P_ARCHITECTURE_LEGAL_DEFENSE.md

# 13. Developer Docs for testing
docs/KNOWLEDGE_DETECTION_TESTING.md
docs/KNOWLEDGE_COMPACTING.md
social-media/

# 14. Ideas folder (future feature plans)
ideas/

# 15. Audit folder (codebase analysis - local only)
audit/

# 16. Sprint logs (internal team workflow - not for public repo)
sprint-logs/

# 17. Dead code & obsolete docs (kept locally, excluded from repo)
docs/BACKUP_RESTORE.md
dpc-client/core/dpc_client_core/backup_manager.py
dpc-client/core/dpc_client_core/cli_backup.py

# 18. Internal backlog (security-sensitive, not for public repo)
# Triaged task list for Mike + Ark + CC. Contains unpatched security findings
# and WIP architecture decisions. See conversations/ for decision history.
backlog.md

# 19. Internal process protocol (CC + Ark + Mike operating agreement)
# Triple-agent collaboration rules, workflow patterns, internal references.
# Moved from sprint-logs/ to repo root alongside backlog.md (S22, v1.9).
protocol-13.md
protocol-13-reference.md

# 20. Security analysis (internal threat models, vulnerability tracking)
# Contains attack surface analysis, key management gaps, persistence audit.
# Private — not for public repo.
security/

# 21. CC bridge internal files (not for public repo)
# Internal cron prompt contains team-specific references (Protocol 13, agent
# name "Ark", absolute user paths). Public template lives at
# dpc-client/core/cc_cron_prompt_public.md.
# cc-out.md is the transient outgoing-message buffer CC writes when the bridge
# send command needs a file (markdown with backticks — see --send-file flag in
# cc_agent_bridge.py).
cc_cron_prompt.md
cc-out.md